fixes N :: real and f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> N. f N = .5 * N + 1"
shows  "f (f (f 58)) = 9"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Define $\#N$ by the formula $\#N = .5(N) + 1$. Calculate $\#(\#(\#58))$. The final Answer is 9
 ### Proof
 We have  \[\#(\#(\#58))=\#(\#(.5(58)+1))=\#(\#(30))=\]\[\#(.5(30)+1)=\#(16)=(.5(16)+1)=\boxed{9}.\]
 *)

fixes N :: real and f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> N. f N = .5 * N + 1"

 proof-
